Finally finished up this 8 pack of Haystack Swaybacks.
I makes these as classic as I know how, right down to the bootlace lanyard. There is just something about the way they feel in your hand that I can’t get enough of. They’re designed to make pull cuts a little nicer, and they’d make a wonderful bird and trout knife. Also, on my quest to get more knives out into the world I reached out to my friend @roughseasdesign to make some leather pocket-clip sheaths for this batch. Words can’t describe how beautifully made,  as well as rugged, these sheaths are. They make this knife and sheath combo truly sing. Thank you my friend! 
These will be AVAILABLE on the website tomorrow,  8/29, at 6:00pm est. 
Check out their spec’s on the site now, under “coming soon.”
Be good out there folks✌🏼

I know I’ve said it before, but my favorite thing about knife making is, it consistently tests your ability and patience. For me, no matter how much knowledge and experience I acquire, there is always something throughout the process that reminds you there’s more to learn.

Take care folks and have a good one.
